dismissalText.commentary: Josh Davey b Hamid Hassan 11 (36b 0x4 0x6 41m) SR: 30.55

dismissalComment.html: up the track and misses it and clips off-stump, but a terrible celebration to follow as Hassan attempts a kart-wheel but would struggle to get 5 out of 10 by the judges.

dismissalText.commentary: Richie Berrington b Samiullah Shinwari 33 (43b 5x4 0x6 53m) SR: 76.74

dismissalComment.html: tries to sweep again and hits off his glove onto the stumps, unlucky for Berrington who batted well.

commentTextItems.html: nudged into the off-side for the winning runs.

commentPostTextItems.html: And thats the game, Scotland win comfortably by 6 wickets in the end! Watts finishing 55 not out who anchored the Scotland innings, well supported by Berrington.

Afghanistan just never came to the party today in all departments especially the fielding which was very poor and could be beaten by many junior sides. Thats it from me Calum Mclaughlin, see you soon!

commentTextItems.html: full toss flicked out to deep square for 1 and then over throws again.
pushed into the covers for one.
rocks back and drives to wide long-off for a couple.
driven out to long-on.
plays and misses outside the off.
yorker well dug out by Iqbal.
nudged into the off-side for a quick single.
goes for a big drives and cue ends it down to third man.
drives in the air to extra cover where Sadiq drops a dolly, not great fielding at all.
driven hard to mid-off for no run.
rocks back and cuts to deep cover.
driven to mid-on for none.
short ball which Iqbal pulls high out to deep square where the sub fielder is 10 metres in and goes over his head.
blocked into extra cover off the back foot.

dismissalText.commentary: Richie Berrington b Samiullah Shinwari 33 (43b 5x4 0x6 53m) SR: 76.74

commentTextItems.html: tries to sweep again and hits off his glove onto the stumps, unlucky for Berrington who batted well.
swept down past deep square for four.
pushed into cover for none.
late cut down to third man.

commentPostTextItems.html: A well made 50 for Watts, well batted.

commentTextItems.html: driven straight back at the bowler for no run.

milestones.description: Karim Sadiq has broken the record for most ducks (3) in ODIs for AFG, going past Shapoor's 2
This is the lowest match aggregate (241) involving teams Scotland & Afghanistan in ODIs
Asghar Afghan has broken the record for playing the most ODIs (13) for AFG, going past Mohammad Nabi
